2026-04-18 — Add GitHub Actions CI/CD, issue templates, and project config
===================================================================

Context:
  The project had no GitHub Actions CI/CD pipeline. Inspired by the
  databrickslabs/ontos .github setup, created a full CI/CD configuration
  adapted to OntoBricks' Python/uv-based toolchain. Also fixed stale
  paths in the Makefile (src/app/ → src/).

Changes:

1. ``.github/workflows/ci.yml`` — Created main CI workflow: lint (black +
   flake8), tests (matrix Python 3.10/3.11/3.12 with coverage + Codecov),
   build check (uv build), and Sphinx docs build. Triggers on push/PR to
   main and develop branches.
2. ``.github/workflows/release.yml`` — Created release workflow: full test
   suite validation and Databricks bundle validation. Triggers on GitHub
   releases and manual dispatch (dev/prod targets).
3. ``.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/bug.yml`` — Bug report template with cloud,
   browser, version fields, and log output section.
4. ``.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/feature.yml`` — Feature request template with
   area selector covering OntoBricks domains.
5. ``.github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/config.yml`` — Disabled blank issues.
6. ``.github/dependabot.yml`` — Weekly updates for github-actions and pip
   ecosystems.
7. ``.github/CODEOWNERS`` — All changes require review from
   @databrickslabs/ontobricks-maintain.
8. ``Makefile`` — Fixed format/lint/test-cov targets: updated paths from
   stale src/app/ to src/ to match the actual project structure.

Modified files:
  - .github/workflows/ci.yml (new)
  - .github/workflows/release.yml (new)
  - .github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/bug.yml (new)
  - .github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/feature.yml (new)
  - .github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/config.yml (new)
  - .github/dependabot.yml (new)
  - .github/CODEOWNERS (new)
  - Makefile

Test result: All 1287 tests passed (12.02s).

2026-04-18 — Full Code Review: Bug Fixes, XSS Hardening, Duplication Removal
===================================================================

Context:
  Comprehensive code review of the entire changeset (51 files, ~3000 lines)
  against src/.coding_rules.md.  Found critical, important, and minor issues
  across backend, frontend, tests, and session management.

Changes (fixes applied during review):

1. ``src/front/static/query/js/query-sync.js`` — Fixed CRITICAL runtime bug:
   undefined ``entity`` variable in ``renderTripleStoreStatus`` fallback branch
   caused a ReferenceError.  Replaced with static 'Graph is empty' message.
2. ``src/front/static/config/js/settings.js`` — Fixed XSS: ``data.host`` and
   ``data.error`` were interpolated into ``innerHTML`` without escaping.  Now
   routed through ``escapeHtmlSettings()``.
3. ``src/back/core/triplestore/TripleStoreFactory.py`` — Eliminated code
   duplication: ``_resolve_graph_engine`` and ``_resolve_graph_engine_config``
   shared identical host/token/registry resolution.  Extracted shared
   ``_read_global_config(domain, settings, accessor)`` helper; both methods
   now delegate to it.

Modified files:

- src/front/static/query/js/query-sync.js
- src/front/static/config/js/settings.js
- src/back/core/triplestore/TripleStoreFactory.py

